lass=usertitle>Riding the Planes</span><br>  Posts: 777<br> <font color=#628CBC>(3/11/03 11:09:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for advice--be nice :)</span><hr size=1> Old post but wanted to follow up on since I just finished 7th shawl on Sunday (and did entire 6th shawl Saturday).<br>
<br>
1)  Runed sea shell.  Be careful if you buy it from someone.  Check the effect.  There are two with the same name but have different effects and you want the one with EB.  It's the only one that works with the combine.<br>
<br>
I almost bought the wrong one and only didn't because the trader was a friend and was at his computer, so we started talking and he had bought it by mistake.<br>
<br>
2)  Swordfish tooth.  I got this on my first kill as well.  Not sure if the mob roams, but we found him at the following.  When you zone in, jump in the water, kill that seahorse on the right, then keep wall on your right and go in a short bit.  Pacify the two seahorses and pull the swordfish (that's where he was).  It was quick kill for us.  BUT, bring a tracker.  60 ranger and 62 cleric handled this no problem.<br>
<br>
3)  Sirens hairs.  Again, no problems here.  As a cleric, I was able to solo the 4 outside SG entrance very very easily.  Just had root, DD, MoR, my hammer, 1-2 stuns and good magic resist.  They never mezzed, rooted or hit me with any damage with 155 MR buffed.  I did get hit with tashania but they couldn't do much even with my MR down to 125.  They like to run when low health so save a dd or dd/stun for that final kill along with root.<br>
<br>
4)  For 8th shawl, there is a cave in WL where shimmering geo's are.  I helped a friend with this part a couple months ago.  3 clerics grouped up and swung our hammers on these mobs.  Was mildly bad idea but fun.  Lots of adds and near death 2x for one cleric.  A couple friends (monk and ranger/druid) came to help the friend, so we had no problems after that.  Didn't need to go too far into the cave either.<br>
<br>
